What would be a better spell idea?<br>
<br>
A usable level 20 nuke RULES.  Well, doesn't help me, but it gives me a nice warm fuzzy feeling.<br>
<br>
Some sort of upgrade at 34 might be nice, too, but isn't needed so badly.  Actually, 34 and 39 are both a little weak, and there's no law that says SoL spells have to come at the same level as all other spells.  How about a new level 36 nuke?<br>
<br>
Familiars are still cool, no matter how they are done.  <br>
I will be sorely disappointed if I often find myself choosing not to summon a familiar because of all the drawbacks of a weak pet, and if they get toasted by AE, the resists are useless.  But it will still &quot;look cool.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ice root good.  I think fire should snare. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Maybe a good ice attack at level 52, and a fire upgrade for the 55-59 range.  Both could be high-efficiency spells with a very short range, like burning hands and chill touch, so that they can only be used with a good tank to keep the bad guy's attention.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umindwarpan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindwarpan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/29/01 9:54:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE:</span><hr size=1> I'd like some usable DD upgrade between 51 and 57. Magic based DD's only go so far, especially on Velious.<br>
<br>
I cant comment on familiars, since we basically know nothing about how they are to be implemented, other than we're going to get them. I'm not a great fan of having a &quot;pet&quot;, but i guess thats not a choice i have anymore. <br>
<br>
I love the idea of the ice based root/dd, but i'm fearing the resist rate they may attach to it. Again, we'll have to see how it goes.<br>
<br>
I'd like to see some form of self only breeze or something given to wizards. Even if it is at lvl 58 or something. Just something that i can do to increase my mana regen.<br>
<br>
Something I never understood was how wizards went from a single target root to getting an AE snare in one step. I'd like to see some middle ground there. Be it an AE root (preferred) or even a single target snare, i'd like to see something to bridge the gap. I'd say a single target snare at 16 or 20 would be good. To get wizards used to the kiting that they will have to do at later levels when groups become scarce <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also something else thats escaped me about wizards is we never get an upgrade to Resistant Skin. We get Elemental Armor, but no 2nd poison/disease buff upgrade. That would be beneficial, and make sense <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'd also like to see some larger multi-purpose DD at 60. Yes, something larger than Sunstrike. Just for fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Adding harvest as a class ability for luclin would be a great addition too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I guess most of these are really fixes that were basically ignored during the Class balance talks a few months back, but oh well, i'd still like to see some of them fixed in Luclin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unicolheartsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nicol Heartsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/29/01 10:15:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE:</span><hr size=1> Oh, oh, antimagic shield, self only large MR boost.<br>
